other_tests.findings: Fluid-filled appendix measures 10 mm with significant periappendiceal fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis.

Two hypoattenuating lesions in the left lobe of the liver measuring 14 mm and 17 mm, and a 1.7 x 2.7 x 1.5 cm lesion in the posterior right lobe; fluid-filled appendix indicating acute appendicitis; no signs of perforation.
